#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "developing monochrome images"
msgstr "編修單色影像"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Photography has a long history of producing monochrome images, and many still enjoy this aspect of photography. While there are some specialized/modified cameras with a truly monochrome sensor, most still use a regular camera to capture a color image and transform it into a monochrome image during post-processing.\n"
msgstr ""
"攝影中有關製作單色影像有悠久歷史，許多人仍然喜歡這方面的攝影。 "
"雖然有一些真正專用的單色傳感器/改裝相機，但大多數仍然使用一般相機以拍攝彩色影像並在後製期間將其轉換為單色影像。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "There are two main approaches to this conversion:\n"
msgstr "這種轉換有兩種主要方法：\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A _physical approach_, where we attempt to simulate how a silver-based photographic film emulsion would react to the light captured at the scene.\n"
msgstr "一種 _實際方法_，可試圖模擬銀基攝影膠片乳劑如何對場景中測光反應。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A _perceptual approach_, where we develop a color image and reduce the color saturation in a perceptual color space such as _CIE Lab_.\n"
msgstr "一種 _感知方法_，我們編修彩色影像並降低感知色彩空間(如 _CIE Lab_ )中的色彩飽和度。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "These approaches, and other monochrome-related features in darktable, are discussed in the following sections.\n"
msgstr "這些方法以及darktable中的其他單色相關功能將在以下章節中討論。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "importing and flagging images as monochrome"
msgstr "輸入影像並標記為單色"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "When importing an image, there are a number of properties that can be used to indicate that the image requires a monochrome treatment:\n"
msgstr "輸入影像時，有許多屬性可用於顯示影像需要單色處理：\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If the image was taken using an achromatic camera, the image will be automatically flagged as monochrome.\n"
msgstr "如果影像是使用非色彩相機拍攝的，影像會自動標記為單色。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "When you capture a scene from which you would like to produce a monochrome image, it can be helpful to put your camera into a \"black & white\" creative mode. This allows you to visualise what the scene would look like in monochrome through your camera's liveview screen or electronic viewfinder. The camera will still capture the full color data in the raw file, but the embedded JPEG preview image will be monochrome. When you import such an image, darktable can automatically flag the image as monochrome based on the preview image.\n"
msgstr ""
"當拍攝場景並要產生單色影像時，將相機設定於“黑白”創意模式會有幫助。 這可經由相機的即時取景螢幕或電子取景器以單色觀看。 相機仍將攝製全彩的原始檔案，"
"但嵌入的 JPEG 預覽影像為單色的。 當輸入這樣的影像時，darktable 可以根據預覽影像自動將影像標記為單色。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "  Checking whether the preview is monochrome slows down the import process, so this is disabled by default. You can enable this check in [preferences > processing > detect monochrome previews](../preferences-settings/processing.md)  \n"
msgstr ""
"  檢查預覽是否為單色會減緩輸入過程，因此預設情況下關閉。 可在 [偏好 > 處理 > 偵測單色預覽](../preferences-settings/"
"processing.md) 中啟用此檢查  \n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "When processing a raw file, one of the first steps is to [_demosaic_](../module-reference/processing-modules/demosaic.md) the image. If you set the _demosaicing method_ to \"passthrough (monochrome)\", this discards color information during the demosaicing process, and darktable will flag the image as monochrome. \n"
msgstr ""
"處理原始檔時，第一步是 [_去馬賽克_](../module-reference/processing-modules/demosaic.md) 影像。 "
"如果將 _去馬賽克方法_ 設置為“經過 (單色)”，這會在去馬賽克過程中丟棄色彩資訊，且 darktable 會將影像標記為單色。 \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "  **Note:** You should only use this for images taken on a camera where the color filter array has been removed.\n"
msgstr "  **注意：** 應該只使用於在已移除濾波器陣列的相機拍攝的影像上。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "After you have imported the image, you can manually flag an image as monochrome (or not) using the _metadata_ tab on the lighttable's [selected images](../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md) module,\n"
msgstr ""
"輸入影像後，可手動使用 映繪臺 的 [選定影像](../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/"
"selected-image.md) 模組的 _詮釋資料_ 將影像標記為單色(或非單色) ，\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If any of the above methods result in an image being flagged as monochrome, darktable modules can use this information to present the user with some monochrome-specific module controls and/or apply special processing to the image.\n"
msgstr "如果上述任何方法導致影像被標記為單色，則darktable模組可使用此資訊向使用者介紹一些單色特定模組控制元件和/或對影像套用特殊處理。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The `darktable|mode|monochrome` tag will be automatically applied to any images flagged as monochrome and, if you have enabled any permanent overlay information on your lighttable thumbnails, such images will be marked with a visual indicator `B&W` next to the file type information. By automatically applying this tag and visual indicator, darktable makes it easy to set up filters to single out images for monochrome treatment, and to see at a glance which images in the current collection bear the _monochrome_ tag.\n"
msgstr ""
"`darktable|模組|單色` 標籤將自動套用於標記為單色的任何影像，如果在 映繪臺 縮圖上啟用了任何永久疊加資訊，則此類影像將在檔案類型資訊旁標示 "
"`B&W` 。 經由自動套用此標籤和視覺顯示，darktable 可以簡單設定過濾器以挑選出可用於單色處理的影像，"
"並一目了然地觀看目前集合中的哪些影像帶有 _單色_ 標籤。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If darktable detects a true monochrome image or one from a monochrome-converted camera (using the \"passthrough monochrome\" demosaicer) some modules (e.g. demosaic, white balance) are automatically disabled.\n"
msgstr ""
"如果 darktable 偵測到真正的單色影像或來自單色轉換相機的影像(使用“經過單色”去馬賽克)，則某些模組(例如去馬賽克、白平衡)會自動關閉。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "monochrome conversion"
msgstr "單色轉換"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "physical approach"
msgstr "實際方法"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "This approach tends to work with linear scene-referred data from the sensor, and attempts to mimic the response of a photographic film with a silver emulsion. It consists of three steps:\n"
msgstr "這種方法傾向於使用來自傳感器的線性場景參考資料，並試圖模擬帶有銀乳劑的攝影軟片的響應。 包含三個步驟：\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Map the color channels from the sensor into a single monochrome channel. Different types of monochrome photographic film have different levels of sensitivity to various wavelengths of light, and this can be simulated by giving the three color channels different weightings when combining them together into a single monochrome channel. The [_color calibration_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md) module allows the three channels to be mixed into a gray channel by varying amounts, and it includes a number of presets that are designed to emulate the characteristics of some well-known types of photographic film.\n"
msgstr ""
"將傳感器的色彩通道映射到一個單色通道。 "
"不同類型的單色軟片對不同波長的光有不同程度的敏感度，這可在將三個顏色通道組合成一個單色通道時賦予三個顏色通道不同的權重來模擬。 [_色彩校準_"
"](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md) "
"模組可將三個通道以不同的量混合到一個灰色通道中，它包含許多預置，以模擬一些著名類型的攝影軟片特性。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Apply a luminosity saturation curve. As a piece of photographic film is exposed to more intense light, its response will fall off as the silver emulsion becomes saturated. This saturation curve can be simulated within the [_filmic rgb_](../module-reference/processing-modules/filmic-rgb.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"套用亮度飽和曲線。 當一張攝影軟片暴露在更強烈的光線下時，它的響應會隨著銀乳劑的飽和而下降。 可以在 [_filmic rgb_](../module-"
"reference/processing-modules/filmic-rgb.md) 模組中模擬此飽和曲線。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Developing a monochrome film in the darkroom traditionally involves \"dodging and burning\" to control the level of exposure across different parts of the image. This can be emulated in darktable by using either the [_exposure_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md) module with manually created [masks](../darkroom/masking-and-blending/overview.md), or by using the [_tone equalizer_](../module-reference/processing-modules/tone-equalizer.md) module, which generates a mask using a guided filter.\n"
msgstr ""
"在暗房中沖洗單色軟片傳統上涉及“加亮及加深”以控製影像不同部分的曝光值。 這在darktable中可經由使用手動的 [_曝光_](../module-"
"reference/processing-modules/exposure.md) 模組及手動的 [遮罩](../darkroom/"
"masking-and-blending/overview.md)，或使用 [_色調等化器_](../module-reference/"
"processing-modules/tone-equalizer.md) 模組，該模組使用引導濾波器生成遮罩。\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "perceptual approach"
msgstr "感知方法"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The other option for producing a monochrome image is to reduce the color saturation in the image, which can be done in a linear colorspace, or in a color space oriented towards modelling human perception.\n"
msgstr "產生單色影像的另一種選擇是降低影像中的色彩飽和度，這可在線性色彩空間中或在人類感知建模的色彩空間中完成。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The [_color balance_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-balance.md) module operates in linear RGB, and allows you to reduce the color saturation in the image using either the input or output color saturation slider -- which you choose depends on whether you want to make any other adjustments to either the color or monochrome image in the color balance module. The color balance module tends to give a predictable and perceptually-uniform result.\n"
msgstr ""
"[_色彩平衡_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-balance.md) 模組以線性 RGB "
"運行，可使用輸入或輸出色彩飽和度滑動條降低影像中的色彩飽和度 - - 哪個選擇取決於是否要對色彩平衡模組中的彩色或單色影像進行任何其他調整。 "
"色彩平衡模組傾向於給出可預測且感知一致的結果。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The [_monochrome_](../module-reference/processing-modules/monochrome.md) module works in Lab color space, and it allows the user to graphically define a weighted combination of colors to determine the density of the blacks in the monochrome image. The interface can be somewhat sensitive to the settings, with small changes producing large effects, and you may experience problems with the global contrast and/or black pixel artifacts.\n"
msgstr ""
"[_單色_](../module-reference/processing-modules/monochrome.md) 模組在 Lab "
"色彩空間中工作，可讓使用者以圖形方式定義色彩的加權組合以決定單色影像中的黑色密度。 "
"介面可能對設定會有些太靈敏，小的更改會產生大的效果，並且可能會遇到全域對比度和/或黑色像素偽影的問題。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/guides-tutorials/monochrome.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Other modules such as [_color zones_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-zones.md) can also be used to remove color saturation from the image, but these don't offer any real advantage over the simplicity of the _color balance_ module's saturation sliders.\n"
msgstr ""
"其他模組，如 [_色區_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-zones.md) "
"也可用於從影像中去除色彩飽和度，但這些模組並沒有任何真正的優勢可勝過 _色彩平衡_ 模組簡單的飽和度滑動條。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "batch-editing images"
msgstr "批次編修影像"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Batch-editing is the process of developing images in a semantically-related series that are expected to have a consistent final look, often with the intent of publishing the images in catalogues, magazines or books. It can be a tedious, frustrating and unexciting task, so darktable includes functionality to help make it faster and more reliable.\n"
msgstr ""
"批次編輯是個編修影像的過程使得這些影像有一致的最終外觀，通常目的在於將影像出版到目錄、雜誌或書籍中。 這可能是一項乏味、令人沮喪和乏味的任務，因此 "
"darktable 包含有助於使其更快、更可靠的功能。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/negadoctor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "preparation"
msgstr "準備"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "shooting color checkers"
msgstr "拍攝顏色檢查器"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Shooting a color checker on-location can save a tremendous amount of time during batch post-processing of a series of images. The image of the color checker can be quickly used as a color reference in the post-processing workflow to neutralize any color cast -- Datacolor and X-Rite color checkers (24 and 48) are natively supported.\n"
msgstr ""
"在現場拍攝顏色檢查器可以在一系列影像的批次後製處理過程中節省大量時間。 影像的顏色檢查器可以快速做為後處理工作流程中的顏色參考，以中和任何色偏——"
"Datacolor 和 X-Rite 顏色檢查器（24 和 48）是原生支援的。\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "prefer consistent lighting conditions"
msgstr "偏好一致的照明條件"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If possible, use controlled artifical lighting to maintain consistent lighting over the series of images. This means that you won't have to worry about light color temperature and intensity changes between images. Shoot a new image of the same color checker every time your lighting conditions change.\n"
msgstr ""
"如果可能，請使用人工控制照明來保持系列影像的光線一致。 這表示不必擔心影像之間的光線色溫和強度變化。 "
"每當光線條件發生變化時，拍攝一張相同顏色檢查器的新影像。\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "prefer manual mode"
msgstr "偏好手動模式"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If possible, shooting in manual mode with constant exposure settings will help to remove some variability in the series. In terms of post-processing, any variation means that individual adjustments will be needed on each image, which will hinder your productivity.\n"
msgstr ""
"如果可能，在手動模式下使用固定曝光設定拍攝，將有助於消除系列影像的變化。 在後製處理方面，任何變化都意味著需要對每張影像個別調整，這將阻礙工作效率。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "post-processing"
msgstr "後製"

#. type: Title #
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/diffuse.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "concepts"
msgstr "觀念"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The post-processing needs to be split in 2 fully separated parts:\n"
msgstr "後製需要分成 2 個完全分離的部分：\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "primary color-grading,\n"
msgstr "主要的色彩分級，\n"

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "secondary color-grading.\n"
msgstr "次要色彩分級\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Primary color-grading is performed first in the pixel pipeline **and** in the editing workflow, with modules such as [_exposure_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md), [_input color profile_](../module-reference/processing-modules/input-color-profile.md) and [_color calibration_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md). Its purpose is to normalize each image to the same neutral ground-truth, in terms of overall brightness, color accuracy and white balance. This stage aims at making all images look similarly boring by removing any color cast and ensuring a perfectly neutral white, and is particularly important if your series uses different cameras. Primary color-grading is not about artistic intent or expression, but simply about preparing a sane and consistent basis for the next stage.\n"
msgstr ""
"主要色彩分級首先在像素管線中執行**及**在編輯工作流程中，使用 [_曝光_](../module-reference/"
"processing-modules/exposure.md)、[ _輸入顏色配置_ ](../module-reference/"
"processing-modules/input-color-profile.md) 等模組和 [_色彩校準_](../module-reference/"
"processing-modules/color-calibration.md)。 "
"其目的是在整體亮度、色彩準確度和白平衡方面將每張圖像正規化為相同的中性標準。 "
"此階段旨在經由消除任何偏色並確保完美的中性白色以使得所有影像看起來同樣無聊，這一點尤其重要，如果您的系列影像使用不同的相機。 "
"主要色彩分級不是關於藝術意圖或表達，而只是為下一階段準備一個沒問題和一致的基礎。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Secondary color-grading happens next in the pixel pipeline **and** in the editing workflow. This is where all the artistic expression happens, with modules such as [_color balance rgb_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-balance-rgb.md). **If and only if** the primary color-grading was successful at perfectly neutralizing all images to the same ground-truth, copying and pasting the secondary color-grading steps between images should have exactly the same visual effect on each image, no matter if the images were shot with a different camera or under _slightly_ different lighting conditions.\n"
msgstr ""
"接下來在像素管線**和**編輯工作流程中進行二次顏色分級。 這是所有藝術表達所在，使用諸如 [_色彩平衡rgb_](../module-"
"reference/processing-modules/color-balance-rgb.md) 之類的模組。 **若且唯若**主要色彩分級成功地將所"
"有影像完美中和到相同標準，在影像之間複製和貼上次要色彩分級步驟，應該對每張圖像有完全相同的視覺效果，不管影像是使用不同的相機還是在_稍微_不同的光線條件下"
"拍攝的。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "In a nutshell, the whole purpose of the primary color-grading is to ensure the repeatability of the secondary color-grading between images. For example, if a non-neutral white balance is expected in the series, it is much easier to re-introduce non-neutrality in _color balance rgb_ (using the same color shift) on fully-neutralized images, than to fine-tune the primary color-grading individually on each image, especially if several different cameras were used.\n"
msgstr ""
"簡而言之，主要色彩分級的全部目的是在確保影像之間的二次色彩分級的可重複性。 例如，如果系列中預期會出現非中性白平衡，那麼在完全中性化的影像上重新引入 "
"_色彩平衡rgb_ 中的非中性（使用相同的色彩偏移）要比在每張影像上個別進行主要色彩分級微調容易 ，尤其是在使用多個不同相機的情況下。\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "method"
msgstr "方法"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "profiling the series"
msgstr "分析系列影像"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You will first need to extract a [color calibration profile](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md#extracting-settings-using-a-color-checker) from the image(s) of your color checker. This profile can then be applied to all images shot under the same lighting conditions with the same camera by copying and pasting the [development history stack](../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md) in the lighttable view. This step needs to be repeated for each camera and lighting setup.\n"
msgstr ""
"首先需要從您的影像中取出 [色彩校準配置](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-"
"calibration.md#extracting-settings-using-a-color-checker) 顏色檢查器。 "
"可在映繪臺視角經由複製並貼上 [編修歷史堆棧](../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/"
"history-stack.md) 將此配置套用於使用相同相機在相同光線條件下拍攝的所有影像。每個相機和光線設定可重複此步驟。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Note**: this process only works with the [_modern chromatic adaptation_](../preferences-settings/processing.md#image-processing) workflow, which assumes hard-setting the [_white balance_](../module-reference/processing-modules/white-balance.md) to a D65 (_camera reference_) illuminant. See the documentation in the [_color calibration_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md#white-balance-in-the-chromatic-adaptation-transformation-cat-tab) module for more information.\n"
msgstr ""
"**注意**：此過程僅適用於 [_現代色彩調適_](../preferences-settings/processing.md#image-"
"processing) 工作流程，它假定強制設定 [ _白平衡_ ](../module-reference/processing-modules/"
"white-balance.md) 到 D65 ( _參考相機_ ) 光源。 更多資訊，請參閱 [_色彩校準_](../module-reference/"
"processing-modules/color-calibration.md#white-balance-in-the-chromatic-"
"adaptation-transformation-cat-tab) 模組說明。\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "editing the reference image"
msgstr "編輯參考影像"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Choose a reference image that was taken in the lighting conditions closest to those of the color checker image that served as your profiling reference. Your primary color-grading should already be handled by the profile used in the _color calibration_ module (in conjuction with the _input color profile_ module). What remains to complete this stage is to adjust the [_exposure_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md) setting to match the overall brightness that you expect.\n"
msgstr ""
"選擇在最接近可當作配置參考的顏色檢查器影像的光線條件下拍攝的參考影像。 "
"主要色彩分級應該已經使用_色彩校準_模組中的配置處理（與_輸入顏色配置_模塊一起）。 此階段的剩餘工作是調整 [_曝光_](../module-"
"reference/processing-modules/exposure.md) 設定以符合期望的整體亮度。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Next, proceed with the [_filmic rgb_](../module-reference/processing-modules/filmic-rgb.md#scene) white and black relative exposures, as well as the contrast setting. Finish with the secondary color-grading.\n"
msgstr ""
"接下來，繼續進行 [_filmic rgb_](../module-reference/processing-modules/filmic-rgb."
"md#scene) 白色和黑色相對曝光，以及對比度設定。 完成二次顏色分級。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "When this is done, you can measure the brightness and chromaticity of a control sample, preferably located on a non-moving surface that is consistently lit across your series (and appearing in all the frames). These measurements are taken using the [_spot exposure mapping_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md#spot-exposure-mapping) and [_color calibration spot mapping_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md#spot-color-mapping) tools. They will be memorized and will serve as a target for individual images as needed.\n"
msgstr ""
"完成此操作後，可測量控制樣品的亮度和色度，最好位於一個不移動的表面上並在系列影像中持續保持照明（並出現在所有景框中）。 這些測量使用 [_點曝光映射_"
"](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md#spot-exposure-mapping) "
"和 [ _色彩校準點映射_ ](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md"
"#spot-color-mapping)工具。 它們會被記住，將來需要時可做為個別影像的目標。\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "propagating the look"
msgstr "傳播外觀"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can then propagate your secondary color-grading (including _filmic rgb_) to all the other images of the series, no matter whether or not they were shot in the same lighting conditions, since you should already have propagated your primary color-grading (calibration profile) to the relevant images. Don't forget to paste the history using _append_ mode or you will overwrite your primary color-grading as well.\n"
msgstr ""
"然後，可將二級色彩分級(包括 _filmic rgb_ "
")傳播到所有其他的系列影像，無論是否在相同的光線條件下拍攝，因為應該已經傳播了主要色彩分級(校準配置)到相關影像。 不要忘記使用 _附加_ "
"模式貼上歷史記錄，否則會覆蓋主要色彩分級。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "However, this alone will not ensure a consistent look for the whole series.\n"
msgstr "但是，僅此一項並不能確保整個系列的外觀一致\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "fine-tune individual settings"
msgstr "微調個別設定"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If there was some variability in your lighting conditions, each image will need some further fine-tuning adjustments. Fortunately, if you have applied the proposed method so far, this should be relatively straightforward.\n"
msgstr "如果光線條件有變化，則每張影像都需要進一步微調。 幸運的是，如果到目前為止已經套用了建議的方法，那麼應該相對直接。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "First, homogenize the exposure using your control sample and the [_spot exposure mapping_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md#spot-exposure-mapping) tool.\n"
msgstr ""
"首先，使用控制樣本及 [_點曝光映射_](../module-reference/processing-modules/exposure.md#spot-"
"exposure-mapping) 以均勻化曝光。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Then, adjust the _filmic rgb_ white relative exposure if needed, preferably using the color picker. The contrast should not require any adjustment since it does not depend on the dynamic-range of the image.\n"
msgstr "然後，如果需要，最好使用顏色選擇器調整 _filmic rgb_ 白色相對曝光。 對比度不需要任何調整，因為它不依賴影像的動態範圍。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Finally, homogenize the chromatic adaptation, using your control sample and the [_color calibration spot mapping_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md#spot-color-mapping) tool.\n"
msgstr ""
"最後，使用您的控制樣本和 [_色彩校準點映射_](../module-reference/processing-modules/color-"
"calibration.md#spot-color-mapping) 工具均勻化色彩調適\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "This should get you close enough in most cases. However, if the background has changed, it is possible that these fine adjustments (aimed towards technically normalizing the primary color-grading on an individual basis) are not sufficient to give a perceptually-even look. In this case, you will need an extra step of secondary color-grading, which you are advised to perform on top of the previous one (shared with the other images of the series), in new instances of the relevant modules located later in the pipe. This ensures that the base secondary color-grading stays constant for all images and makes for a better workflow. You are not advised to make large changes in the primary color-grading to manage perceptual discrepancies involving contrast with the background.\n"
msgstr ""
"在大多數情況下，這應該足夠接近。 但是，如果背景發生了變化，這些細緻調整(目標在個別基礎上技術標準化主要色彩分級）可能不足以提供感知上的均勻外觀。 "
"在這種情況下，將需要額外的二級色彩分級步驟，在位於像素管道後面的相關模組新實例中，建議在前一個(與該系列的其他影像共享)之上執行。 "
"以確保了所有影像的基本二次色彩分級保持不變，並有助於更好的工作流程。 不建議主要色彩分級進行較大更改以管理涉及與背景對比度的感知差異。\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "controlling your series"
msgstr "控制系列影像"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/guides-tutorials/batch-editing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The [culling mode](../lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md) in the _lighttable_ view will help you to compare images side-by-side when the work is done. To view your reference edit in the darkroom view, you may display the [filmstrip](../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md) and increase its height, or use a [snapshot](../module-reference/utility-modules/darkroom/snapshots.md) of the reference overlaid on the current image (which will not necessarily have the same size).\n"
msgstr ""
"_映繪臺_ 視角中的 [剔除模式](../lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md) 將協助在工作完成後並排比較影像。"
" 要在暗房視角中觀看參考編輯，可顯示 [幻燈捲片](../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/"
"filmstrip.md) 並增加其高度，或使用覆蓋在目前影像(不需相同大小）上的參考 [快照](../module-reference/"
"utility-modules/darkroom/snapshots.md) 。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/_index.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "digital asset management"
msgstr "數位資產管理"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/collections.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "collections & film rolls"
msgstr "集合及軟片捲"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/collections.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A collection is a set of images matching a given selection criteria. \n"
msgstr "集合是一組符合選擇標準的影像。 \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/collections.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The most basic kind of collection is a film roll, which contains all of the images that have been imported from a specific folder on disk. Whenever you [import](../../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md) images from the filesystem, those images are organized in a film roll whose name is derived from that of their parent folder. \n"
msgstr ""
"最基本的集合是膠卷，其中包含從硬碟上特定目錄輸入的所有影像。 每當您從檔案系統 [輸入](../../module-reference/"
"utility-modules/lighttable/import.md) 影像時，這些影像都會組織在一個膠卷中，其名稱來自其父目錄。 \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/collections.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can easily construct other kinds of collection based on various image attributes (Exif data, filename, tags etc.) in the [collections](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/collections.md) module. Multiple criteria can be logically combined to narrow or extend your collection.\n"
msgstr ""
"可根據 [集合](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/collections.md) "
"模組中的各種影像屬性(Exif 資料、檔名、標籤等)輕鬆構建其他類型的集合 . 多個準則可邏輯組合以縮小或擴大收藏。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/collections.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "darktable retains a list of the most recently used collections for quick access. These can be accessed from the [recent collections](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/recent-collections.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"darktable 保留了最近使用的集合列表，以便快速存取。 這些可以從 [最近集合](../../module-reference/"
"utility-modules/shared/recent-collections.md) 模組存取。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/metadata-tagging.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "metadata and tagging"
msgstr "詮釋資料及標記"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/metadata-tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "darktable allows you to store additional information about your images to allow them to be more easily searched and grouped. This information is stored in darktable's database and XMP sidecar files and can also be included within exported images.\n"
msgstr ""
"darktable 可存儲有關影像的其他資訊，以便更輕鬆地搜尋和分組。 此資訊存儲在 darktable 的資料庫和 XMP "
"附屬檔中，也可包含在輸出的影像中。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/metadata-tagging.md
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/collections.md
#: content/special-topics/contributing.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "metadata"
msgstr "詮釋資料"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/metadata-tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Metadata (e.g. title, description) is free-format text that usually differs for each image. You can add metadata to images in the [metadata editor](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"詮釋資料(例如標題、描述)是自由格式的文字，通常每個影像都不同。 可以使用 [詮釋資料編輯器](../../module-reference/"
"utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md) 模組將詮釋資料增加到影像。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/metadata-tagging.md
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "tagging"
msgstr "標記"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/metadata-tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Tags are usually shared between multiple images and are used to categorise and group them. You can add tags to images in the [tagging](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"標籤通常在多個影像之間共享，可用於分類和分組。也可在 [標記](../../module-reference/utility-modules/"
"shared/tagging.md) 模組中為影像增加標籤。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "star ratings & color labels"
msgstr "星等及色彩標籤"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Star ratings and color labels help you to sort and rank images according to your own criteria. An image's star rating and color labels can be displayed over thumbnails in the lighttable view and filmstrip module.\n"
msgstr "星等和色彩標籤可協助根據自己的準則對影像排序和排名。 影像的星等和色彩標籤可顯示在 映繪臺 視角及幻燈片模組的縮圖上。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "star ratings"
msgstr "星等"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can give an image a rating from zero to five stars. Whenever you import images, each image receives a default rating which you can define in the [import](../../../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md) module.  You can also mark an image as “rejected”.\n"
msgstr ""
"可給影像評分從零到五顆星。 每當輸入影像時，每個影像都會收到一個預設評級，可在 [輸入](../../../module-reference/"
"utility-modules/lighttable/import.md) 模組中定義該評級。 也可將影像標記為“已拒絕”。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "There are several ways to change a rating. While hovering the cursor over an image thumbnail, you can press a number key 0 – 5 to define the number of stars, or press R to “reject” an image. This is probably the fastest way to rate your images on first inspection of a film roll.\n"
msgstr ""
"有幾種方法可以更改評級。 把游標懸停在影像縮圖上時，可按數字鍵 0 – 5 來定義星等，或按 R 來“拒絕”圖像。 "
"這可能是在第一次檢查軟片卷時對影像進行評分的最快方法。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can also directly click on the star icons that are overlaid on the thumbnails or in the bottom panel. Click the x to reject. \n"
msgstr "也可以直接點擊覆蓋在縮圖上或底部面板中的星形圖示。 拒絕時點擊 x 。 \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "As rejecting an image removes the currently-applied star rating, you can undo the rejection by clicking x or pressing R again.\n"
msgstr "由於拒絕影像會刪除目前套用的星等，可經由點擊 x 或再次按 R 來取消拒絕。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Similarly you can click the first star for a second time to reset the image rating to unranked, or zero stars. This behavior can be changed in [preferences > lighttable](../../../preferences-settings/lighttable.md).\n"
msgstr ""
"同樣，可再次點擊第一顆星以將影像評級重置為未排名或零星等。 可在 [偏好 > 映繪臺](../../../preferences-settings/"
"lighttable.md) 中更改此行為。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "To rate multiple images at once, select those images in the lighttable or filmstrip and then press the appropriate shortcut key, or click the desired star rating in the bottom panel of the lighttable view. \t\n"
msgstr "要一次對多張影像進行評分，請在映繪臺或幻燈片中選擇這些影像，然後按相應的快捷鍵，或在映繪臺視角的底部面板中點擊所需的星級。 \t\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can filter images by star rating in the [top panel](../../overview/user-interface/top-panel.md).\n"
msgstr "可在 [頂端面板](../../overview/user-interface/top-panel.md) 中按星等過濾影像。\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/collection-filters.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "color labels"
msgstr "色彩標籤"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Color labels are another way to classify images, and can be used as an alternative to star ratings or to work alongside them. Each image can carry any combination of one or more color labels (red, yellow, green, blue, or purple).\n"
msgstr ""
"色彩標籤是對影像分類的另一種方法，可做為星等的替代方法或與它們一起使用。 每個影像可以帶有一個或多個顏色標籤(紅色、黃色、綠色、藍色或紫色)的任意組合。"
"\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can set the color labels for a single image by hovering your cursor over the thumbnail and pressing the function keys F1 – F5, which correspond with the labels in the order given above.\n"
msgstr "可經由將游標懸停在縮圖上並按功能鍵 F1 – F5 來設定影像色彩標籤，這與上面給出的順序中的標籤相對應。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "To set the color labels of one or more images, select the desired images in the lighttable or filmstrip and then press the appropriate shortcut key or click the corresponding color button in the bottom panel. A color label will be added to all selected images if **any** of them do not currently have the label; otherwise the label will be removed from all selected images. To remove all labels (of any color) from the selected images, press the gray button.\n"
msgstr ""
"要設定一或多張影像的色彩標籤，可在映繪臺或幻燈片中選擇所需的影像，然後按相應的快捷鍵或點擊底部面板中相應的顏色按鈕。 "
"如果有**任何**影像目前沒有標籤，則將為所有選定的影像增加色彩標籤； 否則標籤將從所有選定的影像中刪除。 "
"要從所選影像中刪除所有標籤(任何顏色)，請按灰色按鈕。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/star-color.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can filter images by color label in the [collections](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/collections.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"可在 [集合](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/collections.md) "
"模組中依據色彩標籤過濾影像。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#: content/preferences-settings/lighttable.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "thumbnails"
msgstr "縮圖"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Each image in the current collection is represented by a thumbnail in the lighttable view and filmstrip module. A cache of the most recently used thumbnails is stored in a file on disk and loaded into memory at startup. The size of this cache can be adjusted in [preferences > processing > cpu/gpu/memory](../../../preferences-settings/processing#cpu--gpu--memory).\n"
msgstr ""
"目前集合中的每個影像都可由 映繪臺 視角和幻燈片模組中的縮圖代表。 最近使用的縮圖快取儲存在硬碟上的檔案中，並在啟動時載入到記憶體中。 "
"這個快取的大小可以在[偏好 > 處理 > cpu/gpu/記憶體](../../../preferences-settings/"
"processing#cpu--gpu--memory)中調整。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "thumbnail creation"
msgstr "建立縮圖"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A thumbnail is created when an image is imported into darktable for the first time, after an image has been modified in the darkroom, or when revisiting an image whose thumbnail is no longer available.\n"
msgstr "當影像首次輸入darktable時，或影像在暗房中修改後，或重新查看影像但其縮圖不存在時，會建立縮圖。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "When an image is imported for the first time darktable can either try to extract an embedded thumbnail from the input image (most raw files contain these, usually in JPEG format) or process the raw image itself using default settings. You can define how darktable obtains its thumbnails in [preferences > lighttable > thumbnails](../../../preferences-settings/lighttable.md#thumbnails).\n"
msgstr ""
"當第一次輸入影像時，darktable 可以嘗試從輸入影像中取出嵌入的縮圖(大多數原始檔有包含，通常為 JPEG 格式)或使用預設設定處理原始影像。 "
"您可以在 [偏好 > 映繪臺 > 縮圖](../../../preferences-settings/lighttable.md#thumbnails) "
"中定義 darktable 如何獲得其縮圖。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Extracting an embedded thumbnail from the input image is usually very fast. However, these thumbnails have been generated by the raw converter of the camera and do not represent darktable's “view” of that image. You will notice the difference as soon as you open the image in the darkroom mode, at which point darktable replaces the thumbnail with its own internally processed version.\n"
msgstr ""
"從輸入影像中取出嵌入的縮圖通常非常快。 但是，這些縮圖是由相機的原始檔轉換器產生的，並不代表該影像的darktable的“視角”。 "
"當您在暗房模式下打開影像時，您會立即注意到差異，此時 darktable 會將縮圖替換成自己的內部處理版本。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "After import darktable automatically generates thumbnails for new images as they are needed. When importing a large set of new images, thumbnail generation can slow down navigation in the lighttable view. Alternatively you may terminate darktable and generate the thumbnail cache separately by running [`darktable-generate-cache`](../../special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md). This program will generate all missing thumbnails in one go.\n"
msgstr ""
"輸入後，darktable會依據需要自動為新影像產生縮圖。 當輸入大量新影像時，縮圖產生會減慢映繪臺視角中的瀏覽速度。 或者，終止 "
"darktable及單獨執行 [ `darktable-產生-快取` ](../../special-topics/program-invocation/"
"darktable-generate-cache.md)並產生縮圖快取。 該程式將一次性產生所有消失的縮圖。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "As the thumbnail cache has a pre-defined maximum size it will eventually get filled up. If new thumbnails are subsequently added, old thumbnails are dropped from the cache. However, darktable will keep all thumbnails on disk if the corresponding disk backend option is activated in [preferences > processing > cpu/gpu/memory](../../../preferences-settings/processing.md#cpu--gpu--memory). Access to the thumbnails in this secondary cache is slower than the primary cache, but still much faster than reprocessing thumbnails from scratch. The size of the secondary cache is limited only by the available disk space.\n"
msgstr ""
"由於縮圖快取有預先設定的上限大小，它最終會被填滿。 如果之後增加了新縮圖，就會從快取中刪除舊縮圖。 但是，darktable會把所有縮圖保存在硬碟上，"
"如果硬碟後端選項在 [偏好 > 處理 > 中央處理器/圖形處理器/記憶體](../../../preferences-settings/"
"processing.md#cpu--gpu--memory)啟用。 存取二級快取中的縮圖比主要快取慢，但仍比從頭重新處理縮圖快得多。 "
"二級快取的大小僅受可用硬碟空間的限制。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Thumbnails are never removed from the secondary cache. You can manually clean the secondary cache by recursively deleting all images in the `$HOME/.cache/darktable/mipmaps-xyz.d` folder (where `xyz` denotes an alphanumeric identifier of the cache). After clearing the secondary cache you can simply allow darktable to re-generate thumbnails as needed, or you can generate all thumbnails in one go with [`darktable-generate-cache`](../../special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md).\n"
msgstr ""
"縮圖永遠不會從二級快取中刪除。 可經由遞迴刪除 `$HOME/.cache/darktable/mipmaps-xyz.d` "
"目錄中的所有影像來手動清理二級快取（其中 `xyz` 為快取的字母數字識別符號）。 清除二級快取後，可簡單地讓 darktable 依據需要重新產生縮圖，"
"或者可使用 [`darktable-產生-快取`](../../special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-"
"generate-cache.md)產生縮圖。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If you choose not to activate the disk backend and select too small a cache size, darktable may become unresponsive, you may experience continuous regeneration of thumbnails when you navigate your collection or flickering of thumbnail images. A good choice of cache size is 512MB or higher (see [memory](../../../special-topics/memory.md) for more information).\n"
msgstr ""
"如果選擇不啟用硬碟後端並選擇太小的快取尺寸，darktable 可能會變得很慢，也可能會在瀏覽集合影像或縮圖影像閃爍時遇到縮圖不斷重新產生的情況。 "
"512MB 或更大的快取尺寸是一個不錯的選擇(更多資訊，請參閱 [記憶體](../../../special-topics/memory.md)。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "All thumbnails are fully color managed. Colors are rendered accurately on screen as long as your system is properly set up to hand over the right monitor profile to darktable. For more information see the [color management](../../../special-topics/color-management/_index.md) section.\n"
msgstr ""
"所有縮圖都是完全色彩管理的。 只要系統正確設定將正確的顯示器配置傳送給darktable，色彩就會在螢幕上準確呈現。 更多訊息，請參閱 [色彩管理"
"](../../../special-topics/color-management/_index.md) 章節。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "skulls"
msgstr "頭骨"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If for some reason darktable is unable to generate a thumbnail, it displays an image of a skull ![skull icon](./thumbnails/skull.png#icon) instead. Don't panic!\n"
msgstr ""
"如果由於某種原因 darktable 無法產生成縮圖，它會顯示一個骷髏頭的影像 ![骷髏頭圖示](./thumbnails/skull.png#icon)"
" 。 不要恐慌！\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "There are three main reasons this could happen:\n"
msgstr "可能發生這種情況的三個主要原因：\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Missing image file_: darktable remembers all images it has ever imported, as long as they have not been removed from your database. If darktable wants to create a thumbnail but is not able to open the input file, a skull is displayed instead. Users are advised to remove images from the database using the [selected images](../../../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md) module before physically removing them from disk. Alternatively you may occasionally run the script [`purge_non_existing_images.sh`](../../../special-topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md) from darktable's toolset to clean-up your database.\n"
msgstr ""
"_缺少影像檔_：darktable 會記住曾經輸入的所有影像，只要它們沒有從資料庫中刪除。 如果 darktable "
"想要建立縮圖但無法打開輸入檔，則會顯示骷髏頭。 建議使用者在從硬碟實質刪除影像之前，使用 [選擇影像](../../../module-"
"reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md) 模組從資料庫中刪除影像。 或者，"
"可以偶爾從 darktable 的工具集中執行腳本 [`purge_non_existing_images.sh`](../../../special-"
"topics/program-invocation/purge_non_existing_images_sh.md) 來清理資料庫。\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Invalid image format_: While the extension of an image may seem to be supported by darktable, its contents could be either an unsupported image format or a corrupt file. \n"
msgstr "_無效的影像格式_：雖然darktable似乎支援影像的副檔名，但內容可能是不受支援的影像格式或損壞的檔案。 \n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/thumbnails.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Low memory_: If darktable runs out of memory while generating a thumbnail, it will warn you and display a skull. This can happen if darktable is run with sub-optimal settings, especially on a 32-bit system. See [memory](../../../special-topics/memory.md) for more information.\n"
msgstr ""
"_記憶體不足_：如果在產生縮圖時darktable記憶體不足，它會給予警告並顯示一個頭骨。 如果darktable執行使用次優設定，尤其是在 32 "
"位元系統上，則可能會發生這種情況。更多資訊，請參閱 [記憶體](../../../special-topics/memory.md)。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "image grouping"
msgstr "影像分組"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Grouping images helps to improve the structure and clarity of your image collection when displayed in the lighttable view.\n"
msgstr "在 映繪臺 視角中顯示影像時，影像分組有助於改善影像集的結構和清晰度。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can combine images into a group by selecting them and clicking the “group” button in the [selected image(s)](../../../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md) module, or by pressing Ctrl+G. Likewise, you can remove selected images from a group by clicking the “ungroup” button, or pressing Ctrl+Shift+G. \n"
msgstr ""
"組合影像可經由選擇影像並點擊[選擇影像](../../../module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/"
"selected-image.md) 模組中的組合按鈕 ，或按 Ctrl+G。 同樣，也可經由點擊“取消組合”按鈕或按 Ctrl+Shift+G "
"從組中刪除選定影像。 \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Duplicated images are automatically grouped together. Similarly, if you import multiple images from the same directory, having the same base name, but different extensions (eg. `IMG_1234.CR2` and `IMG_1234.JPG`), those images automatically form a group.\n"
msgstr ""
"複製影像會自動組合在一起。 同樣，如果從同一目錄輸入多個影像，具有相同的主檔名，但不同的副檔名(例如 `IMG_1234.CR2` 和 `IMG_1234"
".JPG`)，這些影像會自動形成一組。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Images that are members of a group are denoted by a group icon ![top panel_grouping icon](./grouping/top-panel_grouping.png#icon) in their thumbnails. Note that this icon is only shown when \"overlays\" are displayed on image thumbnails. Thumbnail overlays can be enabled by selecting the star icon in the [top panel](../../overview/user-interface/top-panel.md).\n"
msgstr ""
"組合成員的影像在其縮圖中標示分組圖示 ![頂端面板_分組圖示](./grouping/top-panel_grouping.png#icon) 。 "
"請注意，此圖示僅在影像縮圖上顯示“疊加”時顯示。 可以通過選擇 [頂端面板](../../overview/user-interface/top-"
"panel.md) 中的星形圖示來啟用縮圖覆蓋。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "This icon also appears as a button, in the top panel of the lighttable view, that can be used to toggle grouping on and off. If grouping is off, all images are displayed as individual thumbnails. If grouping is on, the images in a group are represented by a single thumbnail image (the group leader). If you press the group icon in the group leader's thumbnail, that group is expanded (click a second time to collapse). If you then expand another group, the first group collapses. \n"
msgstr ""
"此圖示還顯示為一個按鈕，位於 映繪臺 視角的頂部面板中，可用於切換分組開和關。 如果關閉分組，所有影像都顯示為個別縮圖。 "
"如果啟用分組，則分組中的影像由單一縮圖影像(分組代表圖)表示。 如果按分組代表圖縮圖中的分組圖示，該分組將展開(再次點擊則折疊)。 "
"如果隨後展開另一個分組，則第一個分組將折疊。 \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "An expanded group in the filemanager mode of lighttable view is indicated by an orange frame that appears as soon as your mouse pointer hovers over one of the images. This frame surrounds all images in the group.\n"
msgstr "映繪臺視角的檔案管理模式中的擴展分組由橘色框顯示，當滑鼠指標懸停在其中一個影像上時， 此框圍繞分組中的所有圖像。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can define which image is considered to be the group leader by clicking on the group icon of the desired image while that group is expanded. The group icon is shown only if grouping mode is enabled, so to change the group leader, you need to first enable grouping, expand the appropriate group and finally click the group icon of the desired \"group leader\" image. The current group leader is shown in a tooltip when you hover over the group icon of an image.\n"
msgstr ""
"在分組展開時，點擊想要影像的分組圖示可定義哪個影像被視為分組代表圖。 "
"只有在啟用分組模式時才會顯示組圖示，因此要更改分組代表圖，需先啟用分組，展開相應的分組，最後點擊想要“代表圖”影像的組圖示。 "
"當將滑鼠懸停在影像的分組圖示上時，目前代表圖會顯示在工具提示中。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If you collapse an image group and then enter darkroom mode (e.g. by double-clicking on the thumbnail), the group leader image will be opened for developing.\n"
msgstr "如果折疊影像分組，然後進入暗房模式(例如，快按兩次縮圖），將打開分組代表影像進行編修。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Image groups are also a convenient way to protect an existing history stack against unintentional changes. If you have just finalized an image and want to protect its current version, simply select the image, click “duplicate” in the selected images panel, and make sure that grouping is switched on and that the group is collapsed. Now, whenever you open the image group again in the darkroom, only the group leader will be altered. The underlying duplicate will remain unchanged.\n"
msgstr ""
"影像分組也是保護現有歷史堆棧免受意外改變的便捷方式。 "
"如果剛完成了一個影像並想要保護其目前版本，只需選擇該影像，點擊所選影像面板中的“複製”，並確保已打開分組並且該分組已折疊。 "
"現在，每當您在暗房中再次打開影像分組時，只改變分組代表圖。 底層副本將保持不變。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Note:** “duplicating images” only generates a copy of an image's history stack, stored in another small XMP file. There is still only one raw file.\n"
msgstr "**注意：**“複製影像”僅產生影像歷史堆棧的副本，存儲在另一個小 XMP 文件中。 仍然只有一個原始檔。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/_index.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "lighttable modes"
msgstr "映繪臺模式"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/filemanager.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "filemanager"
msgstr "檔案管理員"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/filemanager.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "In the default mode images are displayed in a grid with an adjustable number of images per row.\n"
msgstr "在預設模式下，影像顯示在每列的影像數量可調整的網格中。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/filemanager.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"zoom\n"
": The number of images in each row can be altered using the slider in the bottom panel, or by holding Ctrl while scrolling over the center view with your mouse.\n"
msgstr ""
"縮放\n"
"：每列中的影像數量可以底部面板中的滑動條，或者使用滑鼠滾動到中心視角時按住 控制鍵 來更改。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/filemanager.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"navigate\n"
": You can navigate through the images using the arrow keys (←/→/↑/↓) or by scrolling with your mouse. Press the Home key to scroll to the top of the collection, the End key to scroll to the bottom, and PageUp/PageDown to scroll up/down by a page.\n"
msgstr ""
"瀏覽\n"
"：可使用方向鍵 (←/→/↑/↓) 或使用滑鼠滾動瀏覽影像。 按 Home 鍵滾動到集合頂部，按 End 鍵滾動到底部，按 PageUp/"
"PageDown 向上/向下滾動一頁。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/filemanager.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select\n"
": You can select the image under the pointer by clicking on its thumbnail or by pressing Enter. A range of images can be selected by clicking on the first image and then Shift+clicking on the last one. Images can be added or removed from a selection by Ctrl+clicking on their thumbnails or by pressing Spacebar.\n"
msgstr ""
"選擇\n"
"：選擇滑鼠下的影像可點擊縮圖或按 Enter 。 選擇一系列影像可由點擊第一張影像然後按住 Shift 鍵+點擊最後一張影像。 "
"從選擇中增刪影像，可經由控制鍵+點擊其縮圖或按空白鍵。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/full-preview.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "full preview"
msgstr "完全預覽"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/full-preview.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "From any of the lighttable modes, you can display a fully-zoomed preview of the image that is currently under the mouse pointer by pressing and holding down W. This is useful to more closely inspect an image while rating and selecting images.\n"
msgstr "在任何映繪臺模式下，可經由按住 W 來顯示當前位於滑鼠下的影像的完全縮放預覽。這在評等及選擇影像時有助於更仔細地檢查影像。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/full-preview.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Pressing and holding Ctrl+W fully zooms into the image and also identifies any regions of sharpness in the image that may indicate image focus. For this tool to work the input image needs to hold an embedded JPEG thumbnail, which is the case for most raw files.\n"
msgstr ""
"按住 控制鍵+W 可完全放大圖像，還可以識別影像中可能指出影像焦點的任何銳度區域。 要使此工具工作，輸入影像需包含嵌入的 JPEG "
"縮圖，大多數原始檔都是這種情況。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/full-preview.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Regions in the image with a high level of sharpness are indicated with red borders. If no such regions are found, any regions of moderate sharpness are identified with a blue border. Note that this is not the same as the [focus peaking](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/focus-peaking.md) indicator, which is another way to identifying areas of sharpness within an image.\n"
msgstr ""
"影像中具有高銳利度的區域用紅色邊框表示。 如果找不到這樣的區域，則任何中等銳利度的區域都用藍色邊框標識。 請注意，這與 [峰值對焦"
"](../../module-reference/utility-modules/shared/focus-peaking.md) "
"指示器不同，這是另一種識別影像中銳利度區域的方法.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/full-preview.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Sometimes pressing W or Ctrl+W may not appear to have any effect -- in such cases, click on the image thumbnail and press the corresponding key again.\n"
msgstr "有時按下 W 或 控制鍵+W 似乎沒有任何效果——在這種情況下，點擊影像縮圖並再次按下相應的鍵。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/full-preview.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If you want the full preview to stay in place without having to hold the W key, you can enable sticky preview mode by pressing F. In sticky preview mode, you can zoom and pan within the image in a similar way to the [culling](./culling.md) mode. Press F or ESC to return to the original view.\n"
msgstr ""
"如果希望在不按住 W 鍵的情況下保持完整預覽，可經由按 F 啟用粘性預覽模式。在粘性預覽模式下，可以類似 [剔除](./culling.md) "
"模式在影像內進行縮放和平移。 按 F 或 ESC 返回原始視角。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/zoomable-lighttable.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "zoomable lighttable"
msgstr "可縮放的映繪台"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/zoomable-lighttable.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The _zoomable lighttable_ mode provides an alternative way to navigate large collections of images, but with some similarities to the filemanager mode (described below). \n"
msgstr "_縮放映繪臺_ 模式提供了另一種瀏覽大量影像集合的方法，但與檔案管理員模式有一些相似之處（如下所述）。 \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/zoomable-lighttable.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"zoom\n"
": Scroll with the mouse wheel to zoom in and out of the lighttable (compared to Ctrl+scroll in [filemanager](./filemanager.md) mode).\n"
": Zooming the thumbnails does not change the number of thumbnails per row, so the lighttable can exceed the visible area on all sides.\n"
msgstr ""
"縮放\n"
"：使用滑鼠滾輪滾動來放大和縮小映繪臺(與 [檔案管理員](./filemanager.md) 模式下的 控制鍵+滾輪 相比）。\n"
"：縮放縮圖不會改變每列縮圖的數量，因此映繪臺可以超出所有側面的可見區域。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/zoomable-lighttable.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"navigate\n"
": Hold down the left mouse button and drag to move the lighttable around and navigate through your collection.\n"
msgstr ""
"瀏覽\n"
"：按住滑鼠左鍵並拖動以移動映繪臺並瀏覽您的影像集合。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/zoomable-lighttable.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select\n"
": As with the filemanager mode, you can select the image under the pointer by clicking on its thumbnail or by pressing Enter. A range of images can be selected by clicking on the first image and then Shift+clicking on the last one. Images can be added to or removed from a selection by Ctrl+clicking on their thumbnails or by pressing Spacebar.\n"
msgstr ""
"選擇\n"
"：與檔案管理員模式一樣，可經由點擊其縮圖或按 Enter 來選擇滑鼠下的影像。 選擇一系列影像可經由點擊第一個影像然後按住 Shift "
"鍵並點擊最後一個影像。 可經由 控制鍵+點擊其縮圖或按空白鍵將影像增刪到選擇中。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/zoomable-lighttable.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Hint:** you may find that image thumbnails are slow to load when zooming quickly through a large collection. One way to speed up the navigation is to generate a cache containing all the thumbnails using the [`darktable-generate-cache`](../../special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md) command.\n"
msgstr ""
"**提示：**可能會發現在快速縮放大型集合時載入圖像縮圖很慢。 加快瀏覽速度的一種方法是使用 [`darktable-產生-快取"
"`](../../special-topics/program-invocation/darktable-generate-cache.md) "
"產生包含所有縮圖的快取命令。\n"

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "culling"
msgstr "剔除"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Culling mode allows you to display images side by side for easy comparison.\n"
msgstr "剔除模式可並排顯示影像以便於比較。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"zoom\n"
": In culling mode, you can zoom into images (up to 100%) by holding Ctrl while scrolling with the mouse wheel.\n"
": Pan within zoomed images with click+drag.\n"
": By default, zooming and panning are synchronized between all visible images. If you want to zoom or pan only a specific image, add the Shift modifier to the above actions.\n"
msgstr ""
"縮放\n"
"：在剔除模式下，可經由在滾動滑鼠滾輪的同時按住 控制鍵 來放大圖像(最大 100%)。\n"
"：以點擊+拖動在縮放的影像內平移。\n"
"：所有可見影像之間的縮放和平移預設都是同步的。 如果只想縮放或平移特定影像，請將 Shift 加入到上述操作中。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"navigate\n"
": Use the mouse wheel or arrow keys (←/→) to scroll through your collection.\n"
msgstr ""
"瀏覽\n"
"：使用滑鼠滾輪或方向鍵 (←/→) 滾動瀏覽影像集合。\n"

#. type: Title #
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/denoise-profiled.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "modes"
msgstr "模式"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "There are two different culling modes, which define how many images are shown at the same time: “fixed” and “dynamic”. Switch between these while in culling mode by pressing the \"<\" key.\n"
msgstr "有兩種不同的剔除模式，定義了同時顯示的影像數量：“固定”和“動態”。 在剔除模式下可經由按“<”鍵來切換。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"fixed mode\n"
": The number of images displayed is always the same, independent of the selection length. This number can be set with a slider on the bottom panel.\n"
msgstr ""
"固定模式\n"
"：顯示的影像數量始終相同，與選擇長度無關。 可使用底部面板上的滑動條設定數目。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": In this mode, you will navigate through all selected images. If no selection is set (or if only one image is selected), you will navigate through all images.\n"
msgstr "：在此模式下，將瀏覽所有選定的影像。 如果未設定選擇(或僅選擇了一張影像)，將瀏覽所有影像。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": The default keyboard shortcut to enter culling in fixed mode is X.\n"
msgstr "：進入剔除固定模式的預設鍵盤快捷鍵是 X。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"dynamic mode\n"
": All of the selected images are shown. If no selection is set (or if only one image is selected) the last value from fixed mode is used.\n"
msgstr ""
"動態模式\n"
"：顯示所有選定的影像。 如果未設定選擇（或僅選擇一個影像），則使用固定模式的最後一個值。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": The default keyboard shortcut to enter culling in dynamic mode is Ctrl+X.\n"
msgstr "：進入剔除動態模式下的預設鍵盤快捷鍵是 控制鍵+X。\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/lighttable/lighttable-modes/culling.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Hint:** To enhance performance when loading zoomed images, you can enable ([preferences > processing > cpu/gpu/memory > enable disk backend for full preview cache](../../preferences-settings/processing.md#cpu--gpu--memory)). Bear in mind that this can occupy a lot of disk space.\n"
msgstr ""
"**提示：**為了增強載入縮放影像性能，可啟用 ([偏好 > 處理 > 中央處理器/圖形處理器/記憶體 > 啟用完整預覽快取的硬碟後端"
"](../../preferences-settings/processing.md#cpu--gpu--memory))。 "
"請記住，這會佔用大量硬碟空間。\n"

