msgid "This section allows you to modify settings related to the currently-selected shape:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/retouch.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shape selected\n"
": Indicates which shape is currently selected, and what type of shape it is.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/retouch.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"fill mode\n"
": If the _fill_ algorithm has been chosen for the currently-selected shape, choose whether to \"erase\" or fill the selected shape with a chosen \"color\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/retouch.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"fill color\n"
": If a _fill mode_ of \"color\" has been chosen, select the color to fill the shape with. You can click to select or enter a custom rgb value or use the color picker to take a sample from the image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/retouch.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"brightness\n"
": If the _fill_ algorithm has been chosen for the currently-selected shape, fine-tune the color's brightness. This slider also works in \"erase\" mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/retouch.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"blur type\n"
": If the _blur_ algorithm has been chosen for the currently-selected shape, choose whether to apply a \"gaussian\" or \"bilateral\" blur.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/retouch.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
